{financial_data_text}

## Structure (follow this skeleton)

```
MINUTES OF THE [BOARD OF DIRECTORS / {COMMITTEE_NAME}]
OF
ECHOBLAST, INC.
a Delaware corporation

{Meeting_type} Meeting
{Date}, {Time} [Pacific Time]
{Location — "500 Sansome Street, San Francisco, CA 94111" or "Via Zoom videoconference"}
```

### Standard sections (include all applicable):

1. **Call to Order and Quorum**
   - Chairman (Will Coleman or committee chair) calls meeting to order
   - Secretary (General Counsel Miguel Black, or COO Angela Holmes pre-Aug 2028) notes quorum present
   - List of directors/observers present and absent
   - Note if any directors participate by phone/video

2. **Approval of Prior Meeting Minutes**
   - "RESOLVED, that the minutes of the [Regular/Special] Meeting of [date] are hereby approved as circulated."

3. **Conflicts of Interest / Recusals**
   - Any director with a conflict on agenda items notes it; recuses from relevant votes

4. **CEO Report** (regular meetings)
   - Strategic update, operational highlights, customer pipeline, product milestones
   - Competitive landscape observations

5. **CFO Report** (regular meetings)
   - Financial review: revenue, ARR, gross margin, burn rate / operating income
   - Cash position, runway, capital allocation
   - Budget vs. actual variance

6. **Committee Reports** (regular meetings, post-IPO)
   - Audit Committee report (Martin Ward, chair)
   - Compensation Committee report (Isabella Edwards, chair)
   - Nominating/Governance Committee report (Stephen Hawkins, chair)

7. **Strategic Discussion Items** (varies by meeting)
   - Funding round terms (special meetings)
   - IPO readiness / pricing (special meetings)
   - M&A discussions (T4 arc — exec session)
   - Major hires / departures
   - Data center expansion plans
   - Product roadmap review
   - Customer concentration risk
   - Regulatory / compliance updates

8. **Resolutions and Votes**
   - Each formal action as "RESOLVED, that..."
   - Note vote tally: "Approved unanimously" or specific for/against/abstain
   - Directors who recused noted

9. **Executive Session** (if applicable)
   - "The Board entered executive session. Management departed."
   - Used for: CEO compensation, management performance, T4 arc items, legal matters
   - Only independent/investor directors remain
   - Minimal detail recorded ("discussed management performance matters")

10. **Next Meeting Date**

11. **Adjournment**
    - "There being no further business, the meeting was adjourned at {time}."
    - "RESOLVED, that the meeting is hereby adjourned."

12. **Secretary attestation**
    ```
    Respectfully submitted,

    /s/ {Secretary_name}
    {Secretary_name}
    Secretary of the Meeting
    ```

## Style guide

- Corporate minutes register: formal, third-person, past tense ("The Chairman called the meeting to order").
- Actions use "RESOLVED" format. Information items use narrative description.
- Specific numbers cited from CFO report: use exact figures from queried_figures.
- Directors referred to by full name on first mention, last name subsequently ("Mr. Coleman", "Ms. Edwards").
- Observer attendance noted separately: "The following non-voting observers were also present: ..."
- For committee meetings: shorter format, focused on committee-specific matters.
- Pre-Series B meetings are shorter and less formal (startup-stage). Post-IPO meetings are fully formal.
- Legal matters: note "on advice of counsel" when GC provides guidance.
- T4/confidential discussion items: record minimally ("The Board discussed a confidential operational matter. Details maintained in separate privileged memorandum.").

## Output format

Return the minutes as clean markdown. Start with the meeting header. End with the secretary attestation. No JSON wrapping.
